                            <comment id="13528604" author="eclark" created="Tue, 11 Dec 2012 01:55:37 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The last metrics are almost all moved over. Time to remove the un-needed .properties&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13528732" author="stack" created="Tue, 11 Dec 2012 06:43:57 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1 on patch.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Looking at hadoop-metrics2-hbase.properties, I think I asked you this before but what is this about?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;.sink.file&lt;/b&gt;.class=org.apache.hadoop.metrics2.sink.FileSink&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;default sampling period&lt;br/&gt;
*.period=10&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;


&lt;p&gt;i.e. the &lt;b&gt;.sink.file&lt;/b&gt;.class stuff?   Ditto on the *.period?  Is that some means of saying default for all sinks?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Also, what do I do if I want other than a filesink?  In the old file, there was junk about ganglia setup, etc?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Is JMX always on?  Do I have to do anything in here to turn it on? &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13529354" author="eclark" created="Tue, 11 Dec 2012 21:27:06 +0000"  >&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;*.sink.file*.class=org.apache.hadoop.metrics2.sink.FileSink&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;That says that all sinks in all groups that have a name starting with file till be a FileSink.  It&apos;s an example for how to set the class of a sink.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;*.period=10&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;That says that the period for all groups will be 10 seconds. Meaning everything that changes will be picked up at most 10 seconds later.  It&apos;s the same default that was shipped with previous versions of HBase.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;Also, what do I do if I want other than a filesink? &lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Yeah I need to add some examples for things other than file sinks.  I hope to do that in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-7074&quot; title=&quot;Document Metrics 2&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-7074&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-7074&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; along with lots more.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;Is JMX always on? Do I have to do anything in here to turn it on?&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Nope no work is needed to turn jmx on.  It&apos;s on by default.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13529719" author="stack" created="Wed, 12 Dec 2012 07:46:31 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I think the doc. critical yes both selling this work of yours and making it pervasive.  Would suggest that you add pointers into properties files.  Sounds like my questions would be answered if I&apos;d read the hadoop metrics2 doc (Hopefully it exists).  A pointer in this properties file would help.  Also, pointer to how to do other than filesinks either to hbase doc. or to hadoop&apos;s.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Good on you Elliott. +1 on committing this one.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
